      "rationale": "Three-level mesh convergence study performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw model. Construct stiffness changed by 1.3% between medium and fine mesh; yield force changed by 0.9%. Richardson extrapolation GCI < 1.5% for all QoIs. Fine mesh selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals converge to below solver default tolerances; energy balance checked.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static solver converged to force residual < 1e-4 and displacement residual < 1e-5 for all load steps. Energy balance error < 0.1%. No solver warnings or unconverged increments recorded."
